subSubSection.paragraph:
Light yellowish nicoletiid; adults about 7 mm long, antennae slightly longer. Body covered with scales except on head (typical in the subgenus 
Brinckina
). Pedicel of male antennae with slightly asymmetrical apophyses; this asymmetry involves shape and chaetotaxy. Dorsally with few setae, those inserted on the disc of nota very small and sparse, their length about 1/20 of the respective notum. Male urotergite X with 7+7 pegs, 3+3 of them inserted on the posterolateral projections. Subgenital plate of female widely triangular. Male cerci with 6 pegs arranged in a single row, the basal division with 1-2 pegs.
